        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks JDD for replies to queries [in <hi rend="doubleUnderline">1925</hi>]; would like to know whether teeth of cave rat are of New or Old World type.</p>  
<p>Wishes Louis Agassiz would publish his theory of parallels of geological and embryological development. "I <hi rend="italic">wish</hi> to believe but have not seen nearly enough as yet to make me a disciple."</p> 
            <p>Is working hard on variations and origin of species, but fears it will be a couple of years before he publishes.</p>
            <p>Describes his recent work on rabbits and pigeons.</p>
            <p>The dispersal of land Mollusca is a most difficult problem.</p>
            <p>Confesses he is sceptical of immutability of species; discusses difficulty of proving it.</p>
        </abstract>
